    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Rear Cover - Installation - Flywheel</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26513.3.5" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Flywheel</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, you must always install new flywheel mounting bolts when installing the
                    flywheel.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use anti-seize compounds or grease on the new flywheel mounting
                    bolts.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001427" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0739.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Typical flywheel torque sequence (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align crankshaft dowel pin with flywheel alignment hole.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 10 new flywheel bolts.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>CF series - M10 x 31</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Stripped chassis - M10 x 77</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001428" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06032.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the flywheel (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using an alternating pattern across the center, evenly tighten all flywheel bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_292.xml" xrefid="E30014B">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                using the
                <hotlnk xrefid="e3001427">torque sequence illustration</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001429" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj07/J07002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Checking ring gear for a run out condition</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect flywheel ring gear for run out.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Keep the crankshaft end play at zero in the same direction for all measurements.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Attach Dial Indicator with Magnetic Base onto lower oil pan. Place dial indicator tip against
                    surface of flywheel ring gear. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_293.xml" xrefid="E30014C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Rotate crankshaft slowly in a clockwise direction. Compare total dial indicator variation. See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="E30014A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Compare the result to the flywheel surface runout specification. Replace if necessary. See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="E30014A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Stripped Chassis Only - Place ring adapter onto rear cover assembly and install 12 bolts
                (M10 x 35). Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
